    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1583"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1583">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/73.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The German Ambassador informed this Department that his Government would be
                    especially grateful if through its good offices this Government could secure
                    ample protection for the lives and properties of German subjects during the
                    approaching struggle about Guadalajara.</p>
                <p>Represent to Carranza that the keenest interest is apparent among the diplomatic
                    representatives of foreign Governments regarding the manner in which the
                    Constitutionalists will be able to protect foreign <pb facs="1005" n="889"
                        xml:id="pg_889"/> interests and administer justice during and after the
                    attack on Guadalajara.</p>
                <p>It is hoped that General Carranza will give orders to the end that the lives and
                    properties of all foreigners shall receive special protection and
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
